Snowflake Task
Scheduling
The Snowflake task, COL_DB.COL_DM.B2B2C_PROMO_DECOUPLING_NEW, is scheduled to execute (via the PRD_FN_CO_CREATOR role) every Thursday at 11:00:00am (Melbourne Time).

Master View
The first piece of code runs the “promo master view”. The promo master view is stored in table COL_DB.COL_DM.B2B2C_PROMO_MASTER. This table is truncated each time the processes is executed. The output is saved to a table as subsequent steps require downstream tables to be ordered in a very particular way, and temp tables do not have the same ability to order output as a regular table does.

This process:

Sets up the Date format to DD.MM.YYYY (required as per SAP requirements for uploading journal)

Increases COL_WH warehouse size to XXL (as query takes > 20 min if run on an XS)

Assumes the task is run on a Thursday (there are date filters used where CURRENT_DATE() - 2, which is the Tuesday of the promo week, being the last date of the promo week. This date is required as part of the SAP journal requirements)

If task is not executed on a Thursday, you must ensure the sql is adjusted as required, so that you filter for the Tuesday ending of the promo week

